TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$p1 = random(1,4)/10;
$p2 = random(1,5)/10;
$p3 = 1-$p1-$p2;

$pe1 = random(1,5)/10;
$pe2 = random(2,6)/10;
$pe3 = random(3,8)/10;

$pe = $p1*$pe1+ $p2*$pe2 + $p3*$pe3;

$p1e = ($p1*$pe1)/$pe;
$p2e = ($p2*$pe2)/$pe;
$p3e = ($p3*$pe3)/$pe;

BEGIN_TEXT

Events \( A_1\), \( A_2\) and \( A_3\) form a partiton of the sample space S with
probabilities \(P(A_1) = $p1 \), \( P(A_2) = $p2 \), \(P(A_3)= $p3\).
$BR
If E is an event in S with \(P(E|A_1) = $pe1 \),  \(P(E|A_2) = $pe2 \),
\(P(E|A_3) = $pe3 \), compute
$BR
$BR
\( P(E) = \) \{ ans_rule(10)\}
$BR
\( P(A_1|E) = \) \{ ans_rule(10)\}
$BR
\( P(A_2|E) = \) \{ ans_rule(10)\}
$BR
\( P(A_3|E) = \) \{ ans_rule(10)\}
$BR

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp($pe));
ANS(num_cmp($p1e));
ANS(num_cmp($p2e));
ANS(num_cmp($p3e));

